Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.94,0:02:06.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还未找到任何和太阳系相似的系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've not yet found anything quite like our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.82,0:02:14.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们将开启一段神奇之旅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've joined us on a magical journey
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.63,0:02:17.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,去探索太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the seven wonders
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:20.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,七大奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.05,0:02:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们首先前往土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We first head for the Orbit of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.50,0:02:41.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第七奇观  土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Number seven, Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.24,0:02:49.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2009年11月2日午夜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's midnight, November 2, 2009.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:52.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国卡西尼号宇宙飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Cassini spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.99,0:02:52.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}NASA: 美国航天航空局
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.88,0:02:54.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正沿土星轨道飞行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orbits the planet Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.03,0:02:57.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它拍摄到了土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its cameras capture something bizarre
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表面的奇异现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on one of its outer moons named Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.25,0:03:08.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地质学角度讲\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the Solar System's moons
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:10.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系中卫星都是死寂的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are geologically dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而土卫二南极表面虽被冰层覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and looking at the glistening, icy surface of its south pole,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.15,0:03:17.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来宁静如常\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus seems like a peaceful world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:20.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,突然毫无征兆地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then suddenly, without warning,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.12,0:03:24.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地表裂缝中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}gargantuan geysers of water and ice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.84,0:03:27.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射出大量水和冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eject from cracks on its surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.60,0:03:31.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二是土星一个奇妙的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus is a fantastic moon of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:34.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然体积很小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Though it's relatively small,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.47,0:03:38.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但其火山活动与地球毫不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus is different from the volcanism that's here on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:42.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的火山从地下喷射出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where hot magma, which is basically molten rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.19,0:03:45.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔融岩石形成的炽热岩浆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes out from underneath Earth's surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.75,0:03:49.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二喷射出的基本都是液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus has water, basically, liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.71,0:03:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射出后即冻结成冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coming out and freezing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.84,0:03:53.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此也称之为冰火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so it's called Cryovolcanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.82,0:03:58.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号宇宙飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Cassini spacecraft flies directly
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.29,0:04:02.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以1400英里时速穿过高达几百英里的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through the energetic plumes that blast hundreds of miles into space
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:05.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射水柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at 1,400 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:10.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二着实吸引住了我们关注\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus has really caught our imagination recently
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.74,0:04:13.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然卫星南极间歇冰泉非常普遍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we see geysers coming out of the south pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.83,0:04:15.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在太阳系外围  我们还从未\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We haven't seen anything like that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.83,0:04:16.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹丽\N格里菲思天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.19,0:04:17.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在任何冰化卫星上发现此现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on any of the icy moons in the outer Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.23,0:04:20.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二非常奇特\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So something is going on in Enceladus,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.41,0:04:23.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们想探究它如此活跃的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's active and we want to know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.04,0:04:30.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家计算得出土卫二南极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists have counted at least 30 geyser jets
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.34,0:04:35.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"老虎条纹"地质裂缝中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spouting from narrow geological fractures called Tiger Stripes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.39,0:04:38.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,存在至少30处间歇冰泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located along Enceladus' south polar region.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.73,0:04:44.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最新红外扫描地图显示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A new infrared map of the area
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.04,0:04:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此区域地表温度极高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}reveals warm surface temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.60,0:04:50.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地底喷射出的水蒸汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The heat emanating from the Tiger Stripes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.28,0:04:54.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使"老虎条纹"常年保持高温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be due to the upwelling of water vapor that propels the jets.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.35,0:05:03.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有类似奇观的地方就是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the few other places to witness truly fascinating wonder,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.38,0:05:09.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:15.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在撒雪堆积的滑雪坡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At a freshly groomed ski slope
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.36,0:05:20.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或是电影拍摄场地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or on a movie set.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:23.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看这台造雪机器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Look at this snowmaking machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.90,0:05:26.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像土卫二上的间歇冰泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's like a geyser from Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.83,0:05:30.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷出的冰粒和水珠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All these ice particles and water droplets
