Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.01,0:05:37.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,膨胀的气体也会使水珠冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the expanding gases also help cool the dropls
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.50,0:05:38.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后冻结成冰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and freeze them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.04,0:05:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在土卫二上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the case of Enceladus,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.12,0:05:44.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,液态水在地底空间内加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}heated liquid water in a cauldron below the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.75,0:05:49.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随后从南极火山口喷涌而出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}goes squirting out through some vents in the south polar region.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:50.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水喷射出来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when that water comes out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.84,0:05:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进入外界低温环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and encounters the cold surrounding space
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:58.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会冻结  形成雪花和冰粒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it freezes, forming snowflakes and ice particles,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.11,0:06:01.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像这些造雪机造出来的雪一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much like the ones coming out of this snowmaking machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.74,0:06:04.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以我现在就像在土卫二上一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So wow, I might as well be on Enceladus right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:14.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家认为土卫二上有2个内部热源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists think there must be two internal heat sources
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.87,0:06:18.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才会形成这种冰火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}driving this icy volcanism on Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一个热源是放射性元素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One source could be radioactive elements
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.04,0:06:24.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其衰变后会加热内部温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that decay and heat up the interior,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而保持水的液体形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thereby keeping the water in a liquid state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:30.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第二个就是潮汐加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The second could be tidal heating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:37.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设土卫二就像这个气球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Suppose Enceladus is like this squishy balloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:41.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二以椭圆偏心轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now Enceladus orbits Saturn in a slightly elliptical,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:43.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕土星运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}eccentric orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.20,0:06:45.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时离土星较近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So sometimes it's closer to Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:47.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时离土星较远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sometimes it's farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.18,0:06:49.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当距离较近时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it's close to Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:52.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星的引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's gravitational pull
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:56.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对土卫二形成潮汐引力作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}creates a greater tidal stretching of Enceladus
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.96,0:06:59.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离较远时就不会有这种现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than when Enceladus is farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.80,0:07:01.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,潮汐引力作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That leads to a rubbing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.59,0:07:03.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使卫星内部失去平衡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the interior materials
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.59,0:07:05.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此释放出能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and a release of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.70,0:07:08.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种潮汐力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This tidal friction, as it's called,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.31,0:07:11.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,促使土卫二内部融化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}helps melt the interior of Enceladus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.73,0:07:15.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而使水保持液态或半液体形态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and keep the water in this molten or partly molten state.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.82,0:07:19.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一个未解之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One mystery is,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:23.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是土卫二地表下储存有多少水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how much water actually exists beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.33,0:07:25.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个小型卫星下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Could the miniature moon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:27.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会不会隐藏着一个海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}be hiding an underground ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.77,0:07:31.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们推断地下有一个液态海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We infer that there is a liquid ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.76,0:07:35.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为间歇性冰泉必须要有水源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because there needs to be a source of water to power these geysers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.40,0:07:37.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋可能没有遍布\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ocean may not extend
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个土卫二的内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}under the entire globe of Enceladus.
