Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.08,0:26:10.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在过去的数十亿年间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's been formed over the last billions of years
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.79,0:26:13.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经过一次又一次的火山喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by eruption after eruption after eruption,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.65,0:26:17.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由无数层的岩浆堆积而成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has slowly surfaced it with successive layers of lava.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.96,0:26:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一亿年前  滚烫的岩浆从山顶喷涌而出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}100 million years ago, hot lava rivers poured down from its peak
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.94,0:26:27.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖了几百万平方英里的火星地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to cover millions of square miles of the red planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.06,0:26:32.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坐落于夏威夷岛的莫纳罗亚山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today Olympus Mons is 100 times
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.30,0:26:36.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球上最大的火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the volume of Earth's largest volcano, Mauna Loa,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.07,0:26:38.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今的奥林帕斯山体积是它的100倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}located on the big island of Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.64,0:26:44.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奥林帕斯山比地球上的一切都大许多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Olympus Mons got so much larger than anything here,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.59,0:26:46.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原因有许多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for, well, a number of reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.42,0:26:49.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一点是肯定的  那里有很多的火山运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One is certainly, there was just a lot of volcanic activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.46,0:26:53.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其二则是那里的重力小很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A second is that mare's gravity is much lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.29,0:26:55.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你在火星上的体重会轻许多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You weigh a lot less on mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.40,0:26:58.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以随着山体的增高  它不会塌方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So as the mountain built up, it didn't compact back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.83,0:27:03.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山可以堆积得很高而不崩塌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was able to build up to a pretty huge volcano without collapsing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.59,0:27:08.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第三点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The third and perhaps most important reason
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.50,0:27:10.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是其如此巨大最重要的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}why Olympus Mons is so huge
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.89,0:27:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星上没有板块构造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that mars doesn't have plate tectonics,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.78,0:27:15.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不像地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the movement of crustal plates
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.80,0:27:20.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,熔融状地幔上方的地壳会发生运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that rest on top of the molten interior of bodies, such as Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.85,0:27:25.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奥林帕斯山体积可以增长到如此巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Olympus Mons grew to such a big size
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.53,0:27:30.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为火星上没有板块运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of the lack of tectonic motions on mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.35,0:27:34.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩浆喷涌而出的地点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hot spot from which the lava, the magma, emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.38,0:27:36.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,始终不变\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}remained at one location,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.89,0:27:39.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就可以堆积起越来越大山体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}allowing more and more material to build up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.97,0:27:42.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成一座超级火山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and create a super mountain, a super volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.67,0:27:50.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星现在被认为处于地质不活跃期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars is now presumed to be geologically inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.13,0:27:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是那火山猛兽是真的已死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But is the volcanic beast really dead
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.14,0:27:56.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抑或仅仅还在休眠\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or merely a sleeping giant?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.03,0:28:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,欧洲航天局的火星快车号日前捕捉到了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The European Space Agency's Mars Express Mission recently captured
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.38,0:28:10.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有史以来分辨率最高的岩浆流图象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the highest resolution images ever taken of the planet's lava flows.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.42,0:28:14.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有些可以追溯到一亿多年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some flows date back 115 million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.15,0:28:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还有一些仅有200万年历史\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but others are only 2 million years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.15,0:28:21.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以地质时间刻度来看那是很短的时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and on geologic time scales that's very recent,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.92,0:28:26.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就意味着现在也许还有火山喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which suggests there still may be some volcanic activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.13,0:28:29.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果看看奥林帕斯山表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we look at the surface of Olympus Mons,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.80,0:28:31.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能看到有一些岩浆流之上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we see especially that there are lava flows,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.94,0:28:34.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几乎没有陨石坑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which have very few craters on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.20,0:28:36.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是我们知道  这些岩浆流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, we know that those lava flows are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.19,0:28:39.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最老也不错一两千万年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}perhaps 10s-20 million years old at the oldest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.29,0:28:44.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是喷发运动一直在继续\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the eruptive activity has been going on
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.02,0:28:45.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果不是一直延续到了今天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}until the relatively recent past,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.77,0:28:48.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那也是不久之前才停止的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if not right up until the present day.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.14,0:28:56.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奥林帕斯山也许曾经产生过大量的岩浆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Olympus Mons may have once produced vast amounts of lava,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.87,0:29:02.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但那地狱烈焰般的热度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but its hellish heat paled in comparison
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.66,0:29:04.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与我们太阳系七大奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the current temperatures
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.27,0:29:08.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,榜上第二名相比\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of number two on our countdown
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,则是小巫见大巫了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the seven incredible wonders of our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.69,0:29:17.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它远看像是个大火球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This may look like a ball of flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.45,0:29:19.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其表面是温度高达一万度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But its surface is an ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.36,0:29:21.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等离子海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of 10,000-degree plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.82,0:29:23.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伴随着大风巨浪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with waves, winds
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.56,0:29:25.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及大规模喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and massive eruptions
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.00,0:29:29.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,堪比十亿吨TNT炸药同时爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as explosive as a billion tons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.14,0:29:40.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,下一个将要探究的太阳系奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our next wonder of the Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.24,0:29:44.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既是地球的朋友  又是最大敌人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has been Earth's best friend and foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.08,0:29:47.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它用光和热笼罩着我们的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's bathed our planet with heat and energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.68,0:29:51.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但其释放的致命高能粒子波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's also blasted us with potentially deadly
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.73,0:29:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也会伤害到我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}highly energetic particles and waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.67,0:30:00.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们继续探索第二奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We now navigate around number two:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.06,0:30:04.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极热的太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the sizzling surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.32,0:30:17.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面相当杂乱无序\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The surface of the sun is really quite chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.58,0:30:19.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它持续沸腾  不断冒泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's always boiling and bubbling.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.56,0:30:24.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还从太阳内部\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In particular, there are hot cells of gas
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.15,0:30:27.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放出热能气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that come out from the interior up,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.45,0:30:30.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,散发能量  逐渐冷却\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}radiate their energy, cool,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.32,0:30:32.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后下沉回去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then, come back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.19,0:30:34.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种对流过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this convection, as it's called,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.44,0:30:37.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学  伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.96,0:30:36.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种沸腾运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This boiling motion, similar to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.83,0:30:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与水的沸腾非常相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what you see in a boiling pot of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.10,0:30:40.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在地表附近发生的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is occurring near the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.94,0:30:47.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时至今日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have never been able to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.33,0:30:49.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们终于可以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}look at the sun's surface
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.27,0:30:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直视太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}up close until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.99,0:31:01.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时此刻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this very moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.32,0:31:03.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人造卫星最新采集行动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a new collection of satellites
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.86,0:31:07.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即拍摄我们守护之星的图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is capturing images of our home star.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.86,0:31:11.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些稀有影像让人感觉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These unprecedented movies make you feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.77,0:31:14.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳光球层表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're an arm's distance away
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.19,0:31:19.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经触手可及\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from touching the sun's visible surface called the Photosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.77,0:31:21.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳风暴及其他剧烈活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is where solar storms
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.60,0:31:24.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就发生在这一层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other violent phenomena occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.67,0:31:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你能完好无损的到达太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The surface of the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.79,0:31:30.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会发现那里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you were somehow able to go there and protect yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.71,0:31:34.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常嘈杂  异常炎热  活动的非常猛烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is an incredibly noisy, hot and violent place.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.99,0:31:38.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表层温度高达数千度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are temperatures thousands of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.67,0:31:40.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}格瑞格·拉夫林\N加州大学  圣克鲁兹分校
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.19,0:31:40.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有持续不断的磁暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are continuous magnetic storms
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.39,0:31:43.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并伴随雷鸣般的声响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that create huge, basically thunder-like sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.90,0:31:47.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在最新纪录影像中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this new movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.80,0:31:50.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国太阳动力学观测卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Solar Dynamics Observatory
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.50,0:31:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,记录了一次日珥爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}recorded a Prominence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.74,0:31:57.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一簇相对低温的等离子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a relatively cool, dense cloud of plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.02,0:31:59.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,受磁力影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sits suspended above the solar surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.05,0:32:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,悬浮于太阳表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}supported by magnec forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.41,0:32:05.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如图所示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As seen here, Prominences
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.77,0:32:09.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日珥偶尔会断裂  并散入太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can occasionally rip free and jet into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.49,0:32:14.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳磁场非常强大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our sun has an incredibly powerful magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.23,0:32:15.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是有时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But every now and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.36,0:32:17.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些磁场线会与\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those field lines become connected to hot spots
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.90,0:32:19.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面热点相连\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the surface of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.50,0:32:23.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,受太阳沸腾的内部影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And as the gas and plasma boils inside the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.04,0:32:25.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磁力线会分离或断开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those magnetic field lines can disconnect or break,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.51,0:32:27.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,释放出巨大能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}releasing huge bursts of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.91,0:32:30.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引起等离子大爆炸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these throw up giant blasts of plasma
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.97,0:32:30.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾米·梅泽\N美国宇航局  喷气推进实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.51,0:32:33.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成的日珥有着奇怪的弧度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That come out along curious looking arcs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.05,0:32:34.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这些日珥仍循\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But these are actually following
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.21,0:32:35.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳磁力线的轨迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the magnetic field lines around the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.17,0:32:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆发出的日珥也会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Eruptive Prominences can occur in tandem
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.06,0:32:43.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与另一个日珥相互串联\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with another solar ejection.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.82,0:32:45.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而对地球的破坏力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That can deliver a double punch,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.76,0:32:47.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也将加倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if directed at the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.40,0:32:52.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国太阳和太阳风层探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Solar and Heliospheric Observatory
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.37,0:32:53.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即SOHO\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or SOHO,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.40,0:32:55.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,近日拍摄到一组\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}recently took dramatic movies
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.39,0:32:57.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大规模日冕物质抛射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of Coronal Mass Ejections,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.44,0:32:59.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即CMEs\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or CMEs.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.64,0:33:03.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些高温电离气体组成的气泡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These massive bubbles of hot ionized gas
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.04,0:33:06.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,含有高达一百亿吨的太阳物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}contain up to 10 billion tons of solar material.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.25,0:33:08.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们以几百万英里的时速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They shoot out into space
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.91,0:33:12.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷向太空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at speeds of several million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.15,0:33:18.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日冕物质抛射属于超大型太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Coronal Mass Ejections are incredibly powerful storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.18,0:33:20.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}劳拉·丹丽\N格里菲思天文台
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.39,0:33:22.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光是那巨大的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can be as massive as a billion h-bombs,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.00,0:33:23.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就比得上十亿颗氢弹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just huge amounts of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.19,0:33:29.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些等离子射到地球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And sometimes those big blobs of plasma strike the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.07,0:33:32.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会形成美丽的北极光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and lead to beautiful northern lights, aurorae displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.94,0:33:36.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也会对地球造成相当大的损害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They can also be very harmful to the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.59,0:33:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当日冕物质抛射产物射向地球时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When large Coronal Mass Ejections are blasted toward Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.70,0:33:45.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会触发磁暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can trigger geomagnetic storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.45,0:33:48.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些电离粒子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These blobs of ionized particles
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.79,0:33:51.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会损害甚至摧毁卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can damage or even terminate satellites
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.93,0:33:54.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更会破坏地球上的电网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as fry our electrical grids.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.77,0:33:58.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更有甚者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's more,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.89,0:34:01.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,进行太空行走时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're extremely hazardous to astronauts
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.43,0:34:04.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些粒子会对宇航员造成极大的伤害\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when outside of the protection of a spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.81,0:34:09.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,日冕物质抛射会释放X射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The CMEs generate X-Rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.44,0:34:11.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此进行太空行走时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, if you're out in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.44,0:34:13.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果遇到日冕物质抛射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you would get quite a dose of radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.48,0:34:15.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会被严重辐射到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you were in one of these CMEs.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.65,0:34:18.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是大气层吸收了绝大部分射线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Luckily, our atmosphere absorbs most of the X-Rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.99,0:34:21.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此在地表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we don't experience the bad effects here
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.85,0:34:23.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不会受到影响\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the surface of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:25.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你坐飞机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you're high up in an airplane,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.16,0:34:26.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞至大气最顶层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}above most of the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.76,0:34:28.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦受到耀斑侵袭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you can get a larger dose of radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.96,0:34:31.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就会被大量辐射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if there's a large flare hitting the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.40,0:34:36.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些最新拍摄的影像令人心生畏惧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These latest images are chilling reminders
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.44,0:34:40.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提醒我们必须时刻关注太阳表面活动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that our sun's surface is a force to reckon with.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.76,0:34:46.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在不久的将来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And things may really heat up on our home star
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.78,0:34:48.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面也许会持续升温\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the very near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.49,0:34:55.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳活动以十一年为一个周期\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Solar activity runs through an 11-year cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.42,0:35:00.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2013年将达到顶峰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 2013, our sun will be at the peak of this cycle
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.79,0:35:02.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此也称为太阳峰年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called the Solar Maximum.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.26,0:35:05.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.31,0:35:10.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳表面会爆发超级风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the surface of the sun could create the perfect storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.02,0:35:15.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳曾经爆发过太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The sun has had in the past big solar storms
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.24,0:35:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,破坏了地球上的电网\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that have knocked out power grids
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.54,0:35:18.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并中断通讯卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our communication satellites.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.41,0:35:21.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将来也会爆发更多太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There will be more storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.65,0:35:25.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们这一代  甚至接下来的几千年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They might happen at any time or they may not happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.19,0:35:28.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随时都可能爆发  也可能再也不爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you know, in our lifetime or even in the next millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.69,0:35:29.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们只是不知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We just don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.71,0:35:32.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究太阳的乐趣就在于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's one of the exciting things about studying the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.16,0:35:33.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以逐渐了解太阳\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is trying to be able to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.03,0:35:36.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至可以预测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and maybe even predict the storms
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.43,0:35:37.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即将爆发的太阳风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we see on the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.01,0:35:45.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但太阳风暴无法破坏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But one thing a solar storm can't destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.51,0:35:50.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系七大奇观中的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is number one on our countdown of the seven wonders
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.29,0:35:51.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.35,0:35:55.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是太阳系第五大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the fifth largest planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.35,0:35:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其十分之一的表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One tenth of its surface
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.85,0:36:00.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终年覆盖冰雪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is permanently covered with ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.35,0:36:04.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的内部炽热无比  蕴藏着大量岩浆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And its hot interior has been churning up enough magma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.66,0:36:09.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地表的火山因而持续喷发数十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to keep volcanoes erupting for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.23,0:36:19.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系七大奇观探索之旅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The exploration of our cosmic neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.44,0:36:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将以第一大奇观压轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}climaxes with a touchdown on number one of the seven wonders,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.63,0:36:28.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.44,0:36:38.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,毫无疑问\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth, without a doubt,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.72,0:36:42.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是太阳系独一无二的伟大奇迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the single greatest wonder in the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.95,0:36:43.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(43,205)}{\an4}{\fn微软雅黑}{\fs14}{\b0}{\fsp0}{\c&HFFFFFF&&}{\3c&HFFFFFF&&}艾力克斯·菲利潘科\N加州大学  伯克利分校
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.87,0:36:45.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常适合人类的生存\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is so perfect for our existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.97,0:36:47.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.18,0:36:48.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.63,0:36:50.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有舒适的温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's comfortable temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.80,0:36:52.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是个极好的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just a great place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.38,0:36:57.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球是距离太阳第三远的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth, the third planet from the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.22,0:37:00.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其魅力令人窒息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is brimming with breathtaking beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.71,0:37:04.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟太阳系其他天体不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike any other body in the Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.61,0:37:08.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球有将近2/3的表面被水覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}liquid water covers nearly 2/3 of its surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.76,0:37:12.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,各大洲陆地景观各不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its continents inherited a diverse landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.10,0:37:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它拥有全宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's the only planet confirmed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.38,0:37:20.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最独特的生态环境\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to support life in all its amazing forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.64,0:37:24.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球许多独有特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth has a number of different features
